  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You create a cocoon of sand around yourself or a willing creature, protecting the held creature from attacks and area effects as though it had full cover.<br><br>The cocoon has a hardness of 8, 3 hit points per level, and is immune to earth damage. It can be attacked from within, or broken with a Break check (DC 35). If the cocoon suffers fire damage equal to half its hit points or more, it turns to glass, and becomes useless once the duration expires (though it is still destroyed if it suffers enough fire damage in one hit).</p>\n\n\n<p><b>Mastery:</b> Every step of Mastery after the first adds an additional use of this technique per day, and allows you to defend against attacks from a higher CR.<br><br>The first step of Mastery increases that CR to 5. Each additional step of Mastery increases the CR by an additional 5, but increases the cost of using the technique as a defensive maneuver by 1 while doing so.</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
